#!/usr/bin/env bash

today=$(date "+%Y-%m-%d")

mkdir $today 2> /dev/null
rm today 2> /dev/null
ln -s $today today

cat <<PERSPECTIVE >> today/tasks
HEY!

You get the work you do. If you want to do something else start doing it.

Also:

- No one cares about what you think, unless you do what you think.
- No one cares what you do, unless you think about what you do.

PERSPECTIVE

echo "ready!"
echo ""
